==English==
{{commons}}
===Etymology===
From [[water]] + [[fall]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-waterfall.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A permanent flow of water over the edge of an [[erosion]]-resistant [[cliff]].
# ''(figurative)'' A waterfall-like [[outpouring]] of liquid, smoke, etc.
#: ''A '''waterfall''' of mist from the open freezer.''

====Synonyms====

*[[cascade]], [[cataract]]. [[sault]]

